$tours[] = [
  'title' => 'El Born & the Gothic Quarter — Medieval Barcelona',
  'description' => 'Barcelona\'s historic centre is one of the most extraordinary concentrations of medieval architecture in Europe, and yet it remains surprisingly under-explored by visitors who stick to the Rambla and the Gaudí landmarks. This tour ventures into the narrow lanes of the Gothic Quarter — where a complete Roman city lies buried 10 metres below your feet — and the hip, gentrified district of El Born, which surrounds the finest Gothic church in Catalonia. You\'ll walk over 2,000 years of uninterrupted urban history: from the original Roman walls and a complete 1st-century Roman street still visible beneath a modern market, through medieval Jewish quarters and royal palaces, to the most complete medieval market in Europe, preserved intact by accident inside a 19th-century iron market building. This is the Barcelona that existed before Gaudí, before the Eixample, before the 1992 Olympics — the city that Catalans themselves regard as their true historic heart.',
  'duration' => 180,
  'country' => 'Spain',
