$tours[] = [
  'title' => 'Imperial Vienna: Habsburgs, Music & Coffeehouse Culture',
  'description' => 'For six centuries, Vienna was the capital of the Habsburg Empire — the most powerful dynasty in European history, at its height ruling over an empire stretching from Spain to Hungary, from the Netherlands to southern Italy. The city they built is one of the most magnificent on earth: the Ringstrasse boulevard alone, constructed in the 1860s and 1870s under Emperor Franz Joseph I, is a 5-kilometre arc of monumental public buildings — the Opera House, the Parliament, the City Hall, the Kunsthistorisches Museum — each in a different historical architectural style, a deliberate statement of imperial ambition and civilisational confidence. Yet Vienna\'s greatness is not only architectural. This is the city where Mozart, Beethoven, Schubert, Brahms, Mahler, Bruckner, and Richard Strauss composed; where Freud invented psychoanalysis; where Klimt and Schiele created the art of the Vienna Secession; where Wittgenstein, Popper, and the Vienna Circle revolutionised modern philosophy. And threading through all of it is the Viennese coffeehouse — an institution unlike any other in the world, a UNESCO-listed cultural practice in which coffee, newspapers, conversation, chess, and the passage of hours constitute a complete philosophy of civilised life.',
  'duration' => 210,
