$tours[] = [
  'title' => 'Renaissance Florence: Medici Power, Art & the Birth of the Modern World',
  'description' => 'Florence — or Firenze — is the city where the modern world was born. In the 15th century, in this compact wool-trading town on the Arno River in Tuscany, a small group of artists, architects, philosophers, and their extraordinarily wealthy patrons, above all the Medici banking dynasty, reinvented the Western conception of art, architecture, literature, philosophy, and science. The Renaissance, the rebirth of classical learning and a new confidence in human reason and human beauty, began here, and its effects are still felt in every aspect of contemporary life. The city that produced Brunelleschi, Donatello, Botticelli, Leonardo da Vinci, and Michelangelo within a single century is today one of the most concentrated collections of artistic genius in the world: the Uffizi Gallery alone contains more great paintings per square metre than anywhere else on earth. Yet Florence is not a museum, it is a living city of 370,000 people, with neighbourhood markets, artisan workshops, trattorias serving dishes unchanged since the 15th century, and a civic pride that has sustained this concentration of beauty through seven centuries of political upheaval, flood, war, and the relentless pressure of mass tourism.',
