$tours[] = [
  'title' => 'La Serenissima: Canals, Palaces and the Art of a Vanishing City',
  'description' => 'Venice is the most improbable city ever built and the most beautiful. Constructed on 118 small islands in the middle of a shallow lagoon on the northeast coast of Italy, connected by 400 bridges over 150 canals, with no roads and no cars, only boats, gondolas, and the feet of its visitors, Venice defies every rational principle of urban planning and exists in triumphant, beautiful, increasingly fragile contradiction of them all. For a thousand years, the Republic of Venice, La Serenissima, "The Most Serene", was the most powerful trading state in the Mediterranean world, controlling the spice routes between Asia and Europe and accumulating a wealth that was channelled into the most extraordinary concentration of Gothic, Byzantine, and Renaissance architecture anywhere in the world. Today the city is slowly sinking, literally by approximately 1 to 2 mm per year, while the tides of climate change and the weight of mass tourism threaten its very existence. Walking its calli and crossing its campi in the early morning, before the day-trippers arrive, is one of the most extraordinary experiences available in Europe: a city that seems to exist outside time, its beauty unchanged from the canvases of Canaletto and Bellini, its silence broken only by the lap of water and the bells of San Marco.',
